#: templates/index.html:76
msgid "Our proposals"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:77
msgid ""
"Over the past year, more than 100 young Europeans from 25 different European"
" countries worked together to understand the real-life problems young people"
" experience with copyright and to come up with proposals what to do about "
"that."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:83
msgid "End Territoriality"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:84
msgid ""
"We share the deep belief that territorial copyright with different "
"legislation in different countries is not in line with the borderless nature"
" of the Internet. The countries of the world should agree upon a single "
"copyright standard clarifying the confusion of interjurisdictional issues on"
" the Internet. We believe the European Union stands in an excellent position"
" to lead the way by creating a digital single market. Therefore, we call on "
"the European Union to set an example in harmonising copyright legislation by"
" introducing a single European copyright title."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:85 templates/index.html:91 templates/index.html:98
#: templates/index.html:110 templates/index.html:124 templates/index.html:131
#: templates/index.html:153 templates/index.html:161 templates/index.html:169
msgid "Back"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:89
msgid "Stop Geoblocking"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:90
msgid ""
"Many young people move to other European countries and travel regularly. The"
" Internet and social media have made a huge impact on sharing and "
"communicating with people internationally. The Internet has also made people"
" aware of many cultural goods and services. However, many barriers exist and"
" Europeans are finding it increasingly difficult to have access to the same "
"goods and services that are available in their home countries, and vice "
"versa. For example, when it comes to audio-visual content, it is important "
"to have legally available services that are high in demand and that people "
"want to consume. Furthermore, geoblocking hinders new business models for "
"creating cultural works and needs to be ended to significantly reduce "
"piracy, as it is often impossible to legally access the works people are "
"interested in."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:95
msgid "Allow fair use"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:96
msgid ""
"Existing copyright legislation has in practice proven to be unenforceable in"
" a digital environment. Significant portions of the population engage on a "
"day-to-day basis in online activities such as image sharing, which are often"
" illegal. Besides the effects this has on users it also discourages new "
"businesses from emerging due to legal uncertainty. Users should be protected"
" through the introduction of flexible exceptions to copyright legislation."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:97
msgid ""
"Fair use should have an open definition which would allow for the inclusion "
"of future technologies and business models. We propose the introduction of a"
" fair use exception, in order to enable future uses and allow for case-by-"
"case judgements for copyright cases. Furthermore, basic copyright exceptions"
" and limitations, like freedom of panorama and parody, should be harmonized "
"in all EU countries."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:102
msgid "No automated filters"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:103
msgid ""
"New platforms and technologies help lower the barriers for people to access "
"art and culture. At the same time, these platforms and the content they "
"disseminate create new challenges. While there is sometimes a need to remove"
" content from these platforms, it is important to safeguard user’s rights "
"when doing so:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:105
msgid ""
"Intermediaries must only remove content in accordance with publicly "
"available content removal procedures, follow due process, exercise tests of "
"necessity and proportionality, and provide appeal mechanisms to an "
"independent and impartial actor."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:106
msgid ""
"Governments, intermediaries, and civil society should work together to "
"develop a framework for periodic, independent and impartial reviews of the "
"intermediary’s content restriction policies and assess their impact on human"
" rights"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:107
msgid ""
"The implementation of automated content recognition systems should not be "
"imposed by law. If intermediaries opt to implement such systems voluntarily,"
" it is important that they safeguard fundamental rights, including the "
"freedom of expression, as well as respect copyright exceptions and limits."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:108
msgid ""
"The law should make distinction between the platforms by content type (data "
"hosting providers, publishing platforms, search engines, payment systems, "
"and so forth) and by scale. No administrative, financial or technological "
"barriers should be created for new market entrants."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:114
msgid "Support remix culture"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:115
msgid ""
"The undetermined legal status of remix works that extend from visual arts to"
" fan fiction is a significant issue which prevents us from active "
"participation in a democracy where we are not merely recipients but rather "
"creators of new meaning."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:116
msgid ""
"Commercial companies threaten small actors who manage to attract audiences "
"with their new creative works which are based on copyrighted materials. Many"
" such works fall into a category of transformative works which bring renewed"
" creative value, boost arts and sciences, which is a purpose of copyright; "
"such works are a promotion of copyrighted works, however this potential is "
"not explored and small creators are still treated as criminals."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:117
msgid ""
"It is important to protect small creators from such threats posed by big "
"companies by bringing more clarity on the terms of use of both copyrighted "
"and out of copyright works."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:119
msgid ""
"Introduction of an exception for non-commercial user-generated content, "
"compensated by collective licensing in case of commercial use."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:120
msgid ""
"No copyright claim on digital copies of public domain (out-of-copyright) "
"artistic works in any format."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:121
msgid ""
"Simplified copyright clearance process for GLAMs (Galleries, Libraries, "
"Archives, and Museums)."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:122
msgid ""
"International legal compatibility with the Creative Commons licensing model "
"for digital content available for creative repurposing."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:128
msgid "Open Access & Education"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:129
msgid ""
"We experience barriers when trying to access scientific works for our "
"studies and education. We believe that everyone would benefit from an open "
"access regime, therefore all research that is partially or fully publicly "
"funded should by default be released into the public domain. To further "
"lower the paywall of the current publishing system, we believe that peer "
"review should become the focal point of reform, so that we establish "
"alternative means of validating research besides few large publications."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:130
msgid ""
"A clearly defined exception for educational purposes, both formal and "
"informal, must be added to the harmonised copyright laws to enable all forms"
" of learning, including sharing materials freely in class or during "
"extracurricular activities and even for self-learning. Teachers should be "
"allowed to spontaneously use resources from the Internet in education and "
"show them to pupils and students without a bureaucratic licensing process. "
"Support for researchers in negotiations with publishers to allow open access"
" to research in repositories."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:136
msgid ""
"<b>Unfortunately, our ideas are not heard.</b> There is currently a <a "
"href=\"https://juliareda.eu/eu-copyright-reform/\" target=\"_blank\"><b"
">once-in-a-generation reform of copyright legislation going on in the "
"European Union</b></a>, but lawmakers are too concerned with the <b>demands "
"of lobbyists and corporations</b>, that want to back up their outdated "
"business models from the past century. Without changing much on the "
"foundation of copyright, the reform is <b>threatening to outlaw everyday "
"cultural practices of millions of Europeans</b>. Find out below about these "
"issues."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:144
msgid "Current issues"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:149
msgid "#1: Publishers' right"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:150
msgid ""
"Under Article 11 of the <a href=\"http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-"
"content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52016PC0593&from=EN\">European Commission’s "
"proposal</a>, the press will have a new right to sue individuals -- or the "
"platforms they use to link to publications on the Internet. The “ancillary "
"right of press publishers” (also known as the “link tax”) will allow press "
"publishers to request a licence fee from anyone who shares their links "
"online if the link is accompanied by a description, snippet, or even just a "
"title that could be the subject of copyright! This includes most news "
"articles shared online."
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:152 templates/index.html:160 templates/index.html:168
msgid "Why is this problematic?"
msgstr "Pse është kjo problematike?"

#: templates/index.html:157
msgid "#2: Content Filtering"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:158
msgid ""
"Under Article 13 of the <a href=\"http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-"
"content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52016PC0593&from=EN\">European Commission’s "
"proposal</a>, information society service providers such as Google, Amazon, "
"Facebook, and Twitter will be forced to apply content filtering technology "
"to pre-screen the content uploaded onto their platforms in order to identify"
" copyright infringing works."
msgstr ""
"Sipas Nenit 13 të <a href=\"http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-"
"content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52016PC0593&from=EN\">propozimit të Komisionit"
" Europian</a>, ofruesit e shërbimeve të shoqërisë së informacionit si "
"Google, Amazon, Facebook dhe Twitter do të detyrohen të aplikojnë "
"teknologjinë e filtrimit të përmbajtjes për të parazgjedhur përmbajtjen e "
"ngarkuar në platformat e tyre me qëllim identifikimin e veprave që shkelin "
"të drëjtën e autorit."

#: templates/index.html:165
msgid "#3: User-Generated Content"
msgstr ""

#: templates/index.html:166
msgid ""
"In their February 2017 <a "
"href=\"http://www.europarl.europa.eu/sides/getDoc.do?pubRef=-//EP//NONSGML+COMPARL+PE-595.591+01+DOC+PDF+V0//EN&language=EN\">Draft"
" Opinion</a>, the Committee on Culture and Education of the European "
"Parliament (CULT) proposed a user-generated content exception to copyright. "
"This proposed amendment (which has not yet been incorporated into the "
"Directive) provides that using content already made available online for "
"purposes such as criticism, review, illustration, caricature, or parody is "
"lawful provided the source is accurately identified and the use is "
"consistent with fair practice. Such a proposal is not yet part of the law "
"but our view is it should be to ensure a healthy remix culture and a future-"
"proof internet."
msgstr ""
"Në shkurtin e vitit 2017 <a "
"href=\"http://www.europarl.europa.eu/sides/getDoc.do?pubRef=-//EP//NONSGML+COMPARL+PE-595.591+01+DOC+PDF+V0//EN&language=EN\">Opinion"
" Draft</a>,Komisioni për Kulturën dhe Edukimin e Parlamentit Europian (CULT)"
" propozoi një përjashtim për përmbajtjen e krijuar nga përdoruesi për të "
"drejtën e autorit. Ky amendament i propozuar (i cili ende nuk është "
"përfshirë në Direktivë) parashikon që përdorimi i përmbajtjes që tashmë "
"është bërë e disponueshme në internet për qëllime të tilla si kritika, "
"rishikimi, ilustrimi, karikatura ose parodia është e ligjshme, me kusht që "
"burimi të identifikohet saktë dhe përdorimi të jetë në përputhje me "
"praktikën e drejtë. Një propozim i tillë ende nuk është pjesë e ligjit, por "
"pikëpamja jonë është se duhet të sigurojmë një kulturë të shëndoshë remix "
"dhe një internet të sigurtë në të ardhmen."

#: templates/index.html:173 templates/index.html:188
msgid "What was the problem?"
msgstr "Cili ishte problemi?"

#: templates/index.html:174
msgid ""
"The reason behind this proposal was to remedy the so-called “value gap”. The"
" value gap is the disparity between the large revenues of large online "
"platforms such as Google and Facebook, and the low revenues of press "
"publishers. It was intended as a way of redistributing Google’s revenues to "
"small publishers. The reality is far less straightforward: the resulting "
"proposal will not only fail to redistribute Google’s revenues to those who "
"need it, but it will also hamper our ability as online users to engage with "
"one another on the internet."
msgstr ""
"Arsyeja që qëndron pas këtij propozimi ishte zgjidhja e të ashtuquajturës "
"\"hendeku i vlerës\". Hendeku i vlerës është pabarazia midis të ardhurave të"
" mëdha të platformave të mëdha online si Google dhe Facebook, si dhe të "
"ardhurat e ulëta të botuesve të shtypit. Ajo ishte menduar si një mënyrë për"
" të rishpërndarë të ardhurat e Google për botuesit e vegjël. Realiteti është"
" shumë më pak i drejtpërdrejtë: rezultati i propozimit  jo vetëm që nuk do "
"të rishpërndajë të ardhurat e Google për ata që kanë nevojë për to, por "
"gjithashtu do të pengojë aftësinë tonë si përdorues online për t'u angazhuar"
" me njëri-tjetrin në internet."

#: templates/index.html:175
msgid "Here’s why the Commission’s proposal won’t solve the problem"
msgstr "Ja përse propozimi i Komisionit nuk do ta zgjidh problemin"

#: templates/index.html:176
msgid ""
"No. The European Commission’s proposal will have a series of very negative "
"impacts on the free and open Internet which we all use every day:"
msgstr ""
"Jo. Propozimi i Komisionit Evropian do të ketë një sërë ndikimesh shumë "
"negative në internetin e lirë dhe të hapur, të cilin ne e përdorim çdo ditë:"

#: templates/index.html:178
msgid ""
"In Spain where a snippet levy is in place, Google has not paid a share of "
"their advertisement-based revenues to news publishers. Instead, it has "
"simply stopped publishing links to Spanish publishers. It is likely that "
"other social networks will limit their users’ ability to share such links if"
" this Directive comes into effect, thus threatening our freedom of "
"information and limiting our right to be informed"
msgstr ""
"Në Spanjë, ku ekziston një taksë, Google nuk u ka paguar një pjesë të të "
"ardhurave të tyre për reklamat bazë botuesve të lajmeve. Në vend të kësaj, "
"ajo thjesht ka ndaluar botimin e linqeve me botuesit spanjollë. Është e "
"mundur që rrjete të tjera sociale do të kufizojnë aftësinë e përdoruesve të "
"tyre për të ndarë linqe të tilla nëse kjo Direktivë hyn në fuqi, duke "
"kërcënuar dhe kufizuar kështu lirinë tonë për t'u informuar "

#: templates/index.html:179
msgid ""
"News publishers will have the right to sue individual website owners and to "
"ask for licence fees whenever their links are being shared, hindering the "
"ability of individuals to share new ideas and important information."
msgstr ""
"Botuesit e lajmeve do të kenë të drejtën të padisin pronarët e faqeve "
"individuale dhe të kërkojnë pagesa për licencë sa herë që linqet e tyre të "
"shpërndahen, duke penguar aftësinë e individëve për të ndarë ide të reja dhe"
" informacione të rëndësishme."

#: templates/index.html:180
msgid ""
"Advertisement-based clickbait and low-quality news providers which do not "
"charge to share their links could prosper to the detriment of more reputable"
" news sources."
msgstr ""
"Reklamuesit kryesor të klikimeve karrem dhe ofruesit e lajmeve me cilësi të "
"ulët të cilat nuk paguajnë për të ndarë linqet e tyre mund të përparojnë "
"duke dëmtuar burimet më me reputacion të lajmeve."

#: templates/index.html:181
msgid ""
"This will have a negative impact on competition and innovation: European "
"start-ups will be unable to pay for link snippets, and thus will either be "
"unable to compete with existing platform monopolies such as Google or "
"Facebook or will need to launch outside of the European Union."
msgstr ""
"Kjo do të ketë një ndikim negativ në konkurrencë dhe inovacion: Sipërmarrjet"
" Europiane nuk do të jenë në gjendje të paguajnë copat e linqeve dhe kështu "
"nuk do të jenë në gjendje të konkurrojnë me platformat monopol, ekzistuese "
"të të tilla si Google apo Facebook ose do të duhet të lançohen jashtë "
"Bashkimi Europian."

#: templates/index.html:183
msgid ""
"The proposal needs urgent amendment or deletion, and we need your help to "
"ensure that happens. Join the Copyfight!"
msgstr ""
"Propozimi ka nevojë për ndryshime urgjente ose fshirje, dhe ne kemi nevojë "
"për ndihmën tuaj për të siguruar që kjo të ndodhë. Bashkohu me Copyfight!"

#: templates/index.html:184 templates/index.html:195 templates/index.html:202
msgid "Additional Resources"
msgstr "Burime Shtesë"

#: templates/index.html:187
msgid ""
"Unless we take urgent action our ability to post content on the internet "
"will be limited by a censorship machine"
msgstr ""
"Nëse nuk ndërmarrim veprime urgjente, aftësia jonë për të postuar përmbajtje"
" në internet do të kufizohet nga një makinë censurimi"

#: templates/index.html:189
msgid ""
"The Internet empowers everyone to become a content creator and to have their"
" voices heard around the world. The problem is that some of the content "
"uploaded on the Internet infringes the copyright of other content creators. "
"The Proposal is trying to address copyright infringement on the Internet, "
"but addresses it in a way that hampers the way the Internet has been "
"functioning so far by asking platforms to put in place costly and opaque "
"solutions to pre-screen our content."
msgstr ""
"Interneti i shtyn të gjithëve që të bëhen krijues të përmbajtjeve dhe zërat "
"e tyre të dëgjohen në mbarë botën. Problemi është se disa nga përmbajtjet e "
"ngarkuara në internet cenojnë të drejtën e autorit të krijuesve të tjerë të "
"përmbajtjes. Propozimi është duke u përpjekur të adresojë shkeljen e të "
"drejtës së autorit në internet, por e trajton atë në një mënyrë që pengon "
"mënyrën se si Interneti ka funksionuar deri tani duke i kërkuar platformave "
"për të vendosur zgjidhje të kushtueshme dhe të paqarta për të paracaktuar "
"përmbajtjen tonë."

#: templates/index.html:190
msgid "The proposal is problematic…"
msgstr "Propozimi është problematik..."

#: templates/index.html:191
msgid ""
"If you have ever uploaded content to social media, or watched a creative "
"video someone else uploaded, this proposed reform could affect you. This "
"proposal would require intermediaries such as Facebook and YouTube to "
"constantly police their platforms with censorship machines, often with no "
"human element involved in the process. These mechanisms will be expensive to"
" implement. They will make it harder for European start-ups to grow, and for"
" individuals to understand how their content is being manipulated."
msgstr ""
"Nëse ke ngarkuar ndonjëherë përmbajtje në mediat sociale, ose ke parë një "
"video kreative që dikush tjetër ka ngarkuar, kjo reformë e propozuar mund të"
" ndikojë tek ju. Ky propozim do t'u kërkonte ndërmjetësve të tillë si "
"Facebook dhe YouTube që vazhdimisht të mbikëqyrin platformat e tyre me "
"makina censurimi, shpesh pa elementë njerëzorë të përfshirë në këtë proces. "
"Këto mekanizma do të jenë të shtrenjta për t'u implementuar. Ata do ta bëjnë"
" më të vështirë rritjen e sipërmarrjeve Europiane dhe individët do ta kenë "
"më të vështirë të kuptojnë se si përmbajtja e tyre po manipulohet."

#: templates/index.html:192
msgid "Will the proposal fix the problem?"
msgstr "A do ta rregullojë propozimi problemin?"

#: templates/index.html:193
msgid ""
"No. The proposed censorship machines are a disproportionate and ineffective "
"‘solution’ to the problem. We know this, because in the case of SABAM v "
"Netlog, the Court of Justice of the European Union ruled social networks and"
" other web hosting providers cannot be required to monitor and filter "
"activities that occur on their sites to prevent copyright infringement. This"
" would be a breach of freedom of expression and of privacy (CJEU C-360/10)."
msgstr ""
"Jo. Makinat e propozuara të censurës janë një 'zgjidhje' joproporcionale dhe"
