msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:10
msgid ""
"#Copyfighters is a grassroots campaign which highlights the need to amend "
"the European Commission’s proposed Directive on Copyright in the Digital "
"Single Market."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:11
msgid ""
"Unless we take urgent action, the proposed Directive will harm innovation "
"and threaten our fundamental rights of access to information, freedom of "
"communication, and privacy."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:12
msgid ""
"We promote legislation that will make it easier for everyone to use the "
"Internet for education, entertainment, commerce, and communication."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:13
msgid ""
"This toolkit explains how you can participate in the action month online or "
"by hosting an event in your own country, and also offers advice on what "
"copyright reform we think would work best. You can read this guide from "
"start to finish, or dive into the sections that interest you. If you have "
"questions, please contact us: team@copyfighters.eu."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:18
msgid "What we want"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:19
msgid ""
"We want a Europe where sharing, innovation, and copyright go hand in hand."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:20
msgid ""
"The European Union is moving forward with proposals to reform copyright law "
"to make it apply more uniformly across the Single Market. The current "
"proposal for a Directive on Copyright in the Digital Single Market is "
"problematic because:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:22
msgid "… our ability to share news content online will be hampered"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:23
msgid ""
"… our ability to post content on the Internet will be limited by a "
"censorship machine"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:24
msgid ""
"… our innocent remixes and user-generated content will keep infringing "
"copyright"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:26
msgid "We\\'re not asking to legalise plagiarism, theft, or piracy."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:26
msgid ""
"We are asking for the EU to be sensible and not endanger our freedoms to "
"share and communicate information."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:27
msgid ""
"The European Parliament’s pivotal vote on this Proposal is at the beginning "
"of 2018."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:27
msgid ""
"The time is thus now to take action to safeguard human rights and to protect"
" our ability to access culture."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:32
msgid "Who can make it happen"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:33
msgid ""
"What needs to change in your country, and who can make it happen? Join the "
"copyfight by finding your key targets, identifying allies and applying "
"pressure, exposing concerns, and stimulating them to think about and act on "
"#Copyfighter’s key demands."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:34
msgid ""
"Choose the right channels to reach them. It might be via social media, a "
"meeting, email, the media — or all of the above!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:35
msgid "Government"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:36
msgid ""
"Seek out your President, Prime Minister, Member of the European Parliament, "
"or any key ministers or ministry officials that can affect information "
"communication technologies and Internet rights in areas like culture, media,"
" or intellectual property. These are the people who draft new policies and "
"have power to prioritise them."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:37
msgid "Private Sector"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:38
msgid ""
"Businesses can be either targets or allies (or both). They can partner with "
"government and support policies to encourage competition — or they can "
"pressure governments to adopt policies which protect their interests and "
"harm ordinary Internet users. Small content producers, niche publishers, and"
" streaming video service providers will likely agree that copyright reform "
"is urgently needed."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:39
msgid "Media"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:40
msgid ""
"Journalists from newspapers, radio, and all variety of media and blogs need "
"to help communicate why a user-generated content exception is so important. "
"They can also pressure government to follow up on promises."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:41
msgid "Civil Society"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:42
msgid ""
"Greater understanding of supranational, national, local, and rural Internet "
"use helps inform better policy and good arguments for why copyright reform. "
"Universities, think tanks, research institutes, and foundations can be "
"allies, at home and abroad."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:43
msgid "Web Community"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:44
msgid ""
"Which other organisations, bloggers, hackers, and web defenders can support "
"our activities? Connect and partner with everyone who feels strongly about "
"there being user-generated content on the Internet, especially those who "
"have uploaded lawful content previously and had it censored, and demand "
"action from governments and content platforms."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:49
msgid "Social media guide"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:50
msgid ""
"Much of our activity takes place through social media. Here are some quick "
"tips on how to get social with #Copyfighters:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:52
msgid ""
"Add a #Copyfighters “Twibbon” to your profile picture on Twitter and "
"Facebook."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:53
msgid ""
"Make noise using the hashtags #Copyfighters or #JoinTheCopyfight targeting "
"key influencers"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:54
msgid ""
"Say YES to the #Copyfighters Facebook event and share it with friends, even "
"if you cannot travel to Brussels. We’ll have remote participation!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:55
msgid ""
"Share and remix photos, logos, and infographics to raise awareness. Please "
"circulate our memes!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:56
msgid "If you attend a #Copyfighters event, live tweet and blog it!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:57
msgid "Follow @Copyfighters on Twitter and JoinTheCopyfight on Facebook."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:58
msgid "Connect with other #Copyfighters and support their campaign efforts!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:60
msgid "Images for sharing"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:61
msgid "Photos from the Copyfighters camp"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:66
msgid "Memes"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:67
msgid "Download all our memes as a zip file"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:68
msgid "More Tips"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:70
msgid ""
"Connect with targets and allies on social media. Without spamming and being "
"courteous, engage with them on the issues and what needs to happen. Praise "
"them for actions you agree with. Remember we are running a positive, "
"evidence-informed campaign!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:71
msgid ""
"Who can help amplify our message in your local Twittersphere or blogosphere?"
" Reach out to influencers with a large audience and encourage them to "
"#JoinTheCopyfight."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:72
msgid ""
"If you notice a popular viral video is removed from YouTube, reach out to "
"the content creator and share with them information on what has happened -- "
"and how things could be about to get a whole lot worse!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:74
msgid "Hashtags"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:75
msgid ""
"Use the official #JoinTheCopyfight hashtag in all tweets, and also tag "
"@Copyfighters — people supporting the campaign will be watching and re-"
"tweeting."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:80
msgid "Plan your own event"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:81
msgid "Take part in the Copyfighters campaign"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:82
msgid ""
"Would you like to join the campaign by hosting an event? You don’t need "
"special permission or credentials to host a #Copyfighters event. Everyone "
"can support the campaign by drawing attention to the need for copyright "
"reform in their own way."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:84
msgid "Visit the campaign homepage for updates and toolkit additions."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:85
msgid "Register your event and we will help you spread the word."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:86
msgid "See our map of events to see what is happening near you."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:88
msgid ""
"Anyone can organise an activity to encourage others to #JoinTheCopyfight — "
"big and small, quiet or loud, they all make a difference! Events during the "
"action month are meant to amplify long-term efforts for change. Please note "
"that we need everyone to share photos of activities as they happen via "
"Facebook and Twitter with the hashtag #JoinTheCopyfight and tagging us at "
"@Copyfighters. This will help us show leaders just how many of us care about"
" copyright reform, and will make calls for action harder to dismiss."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:89
msgid "Planning your event"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:91
msgid "Step 1: Goals"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:92
msgid ""
"Define your objective and how it will help bring about copyright reform in "
"your country or at the EU level. Determine who you will be targeting with "
"your message, and how many people you will affect."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:93
msgid "Step 2: Event"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:94
msgid ""
"Write an approximate timetable for the event from beginning to end, and "
"consider whether it will be engaging, entertaining, and meet your goals from"
" Step 1."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:95
msgid "Step 3: Budget"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:96
msgid ""
"Is there a free venue available? Do you need refreshments, printed handouts,"
" or anything else that could cost money?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:97
msgid "Step 4: Invitations"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:98
msgid ""
"Think about your target participants and partners. What are their interests?"
" How can you approach them? In our experience, it is best if you can reach "
"out to people individually at least one week in advance."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:99
msgid "Step 5: Communicating"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:100
msgid ""
"Team meeting - does everyone understand the objective of your event as well "
"as how it forms part of a regional #Copyfighters campaign? Download campaign"
" logos and materials."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:101
msgid "Step 6: The Big Day"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:102
msgid ""
"Good luck! Be open to feedback and to revising your event strategy as you go"
" if something isn’t working well."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:103
msgid "Step 7: Sharing"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:104
msgid ""
"Document your activity immediately for maximum visibility and impact. We "
"need everyone to share photos of activities as they happen via Facebook and "
"Twitter with the hashtag #JoinTheCopyfight and tagging @Copyfighters. Write "
"a summary of the event immediately after to publish on your own website, in "
"social media, or on a blogging platform like Medium. Send us your link by "
"email or by tagging @Copyfighters on Twitter."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:105
msgid "Step 8: Friending"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:106
msgid ""
"Encourage participants to stay in touch with the #Copyfight and also to get "
"involved with regional and international activities via our website mailing "
"list, if they are interested."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:107
msgid "Step 9: Evaluating"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:108
msgid ""
"Be honest, what did you really achieve? Are there things you learned or "
"accomplished that surprised you? What would you do differently next time? "
"Let us know!"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:114
msgid "Media advice"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:115
msgid ""
"We want to help you get your own activities and the #Copyfighters campaign "
"mentioned in the media. Journalists often choose what stories they cover "
"based on a press release. We have many press releases [LINK], and encourage "
"you to share them with reporters in your country. (If journalists in your "
"country do not always speak English, we’d appreciate it if you’d translate "
"the press release into your local language.)"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:116
msgid "Some tips for working with the media:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:118
msgid ""
"Find the contact details for the right journalists first. Have you seen a "
"related news story? Open the article and check for the byline; it should "
"have the name of the reporter who wrote the piece. If you google their name "
"along with their publication’s name and the word ‘email’, you can often find"
" their email address."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:119
msgid "Otherwise, try to speak to a news editor."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:120
msgid ""
"It is a good idea to try and call a reporter to explain why your story is "
"important. Reporters are busy and may get hundreds of emails a day. A quick "
"phone call is the best way to make sure they hear you."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:121
msgid ""
"You probably won’t get to talk for long, so think about what you will say, "
"and particularly why their audience will be interested. It is okay to script"
" your call in advance if you are new to calling a journalist."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:122
msgid ""
"The reporter may ask you to email them a press release, or call back later "
"for an interview. Or, they may not be interested at all."
msgstr ""

#: templates/toolkit.html:123
msgid "Good luck! If you have questions, you can always contact us."
msgstr ""
